Questions will be closed. -->\r\nBug with [WHATWG URL API](https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v8.x/docs/api/url.html#url_the_whatwg_url_api) provided by native `url` module.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n```js modules\r\n// ES6\r\n\r\nimport { URL } from 'url';\r\n\r\nconsole.log(typeof URL); // undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\n```js modules\r\n// CommonJS\r\n\r\nconst { URL } = require('url');\r\n\r\nconsole.log(typeof URL); // undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\n**If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce.**\r\nI provided code above, is it a normal behavior and we should use [Web API URL](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL/URL) or [WHATWG URL API](https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v8.x/docs/api/url.html#url_the_whatwg_url_api) should be provided through `url` module?\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n```js\r\n// ES6 modules\r\n\r\nimport { URL } from 'url';\r\n\r\nconsole.log(typeof URL); // function\r\n```\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// CommonJS modules\r\n\r\nconst { URL } = require('url');\r\n\r\nconsole.log(typeof URL); // function\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Please mention your webpack and Operating System version.**\r\n\r\nnode 8.2.1\r\nwebpack 3.3.0\r\nmacOS Sierra 10.12.6\n\n---\n\nThis issue was moved from webpack/webpack#5372 by @sokra.
